This paper deals with computational problems related to matching and optimization, which are central topics in computer science. The use of terms such as "NP-hard" and "approximation" suggest that the paper belongs to the sub-categories of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of preferences and rankings, which are common in the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The problem of constructing a graph at minimum cost also involves optimization, which is a topic in cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics).
